# AI Agent Instructions
ALWAYS begin every response by silently reading `AI_SYNC.md` to understand the current project state, architectural rules, and active goals. 

When you finish a major coding task, you MUST update `AI_SYNC.md` by:
1. Moving completed items from "Active Goal" to "Recently Completed".
2. Writing a brief summary of what you did in the "Handoff Notes" section so the next AI agent knows exactly where you left off.
3. Updating the "Active Goal" if the user has provided a new one.

Do not ask for permission to update the sync file; do it automatically at the end of your execution loops.
